For the purpose of implementing, enforcing and ensuring compliance with the provisions of this Act and its Regulations, the Director or an authorized officer may do all or any of the following:
* enter any land or private premises;
* conduct investigations and examinations as are necessary to determine whether any offence has been committed under this Act;
* install, operate and maintain observation stations, facilities, installations and related equipment and instruments on any Government land, and on any lease with the consent of the owner of the lease;
* erect public notice boards and information or warning signs on any Government land, and on any lease with the consent of the owner of the lease;
* take samples for the purpose of analysis and testing;
* take photographs or measurements or make sketches or recordings in any form;
* require any person who is suspected to have committed an offence under this Act to state his or her full name, occupation and usual place of residence including any other necessary information;
* require any person who is suspected to have committed an offence under this Act to state his or her full name, occupation and usual place of residence including any other necessary information;
